pokemon.name: treecko
pokemon.text_entry: Treecko is cool, calm, and collected—it never panics under any situation. If a bigger foe were to glare at this Pokémon, it would glare right back without conceding an inch of ground.

pokemon.name: grovyle
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon adeptly flies from branch to branch in trees. In a forest, no Pokémon can ever hope to catch a fleeing Grovyle however fast they may be.

pokemon.name: sceptile
pokemon.text_entry: Sceptile has seeds growing on its back. They are said to be bursting with nutrients that revitalize trees. This Pokémon raises the trees in a forest with loving care.

pokemon.name: torchic
pokemon.text_entry: Torchic has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug—it will be glowing with warmth. This Pokémon is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

pokemon.name: combusken
pokemon.text_entry: Combusken battles with the intensely hot flames it spews from its beak and with outstandingly destructive kicks. This Pokémon’s cry is very loud and distracting.

pokemon.name: blaziken
pokemon.text_entry: Blaziken has incredibly strong legs—it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This Pokémon’s blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

pokemon.name: mudkip
pokemon.text_entry: In water, Mudkip breathes using the gills on its cheeks. If it is faced with a tight situation in battle, this Pokémon will unleash its amazing power—it can crush rocks bigger than itself.

pokemon.name: marshtomp
pokemon.text_entry: Marshtomp is much faster at traveling through mud than it is at swimming. This Pokémon’s hindquarters exhibit obvious development, giving it the ability to walk on just its hind legs.

pokemon.name: swampert
pokemon.text_entry: Swampert predicts storms by sensing subtle differences in the sounds of waves and tidal winds with its fins. If a storm is approaching, it piles up boulders to protect itself.

pokemon.name: poochyena
pokemon.text_entry: Poochyena is an omnivore—it will eat anything. A distinguishing feature is how large its fangs are compared to its body. This Pokémon tries to intimidate its foes by making the hair on its tail bristle out.

pokemon.name: mightyena
pokemon.text_entry: Mightyena travel and act as a pack in the wild. The memory of its life in the wild compels the Pokémon to obey only those Trainers that it recognizes to possess superior skill.

pokemon.name: zigzagoon
pokemon.text_entry: Zigzagoon that adapted to regions outside Galar acquired this appearance. If you’ve lost something, this Pokémon can likely find it.

pokemon.name: linoone
pokemon.text_entry: This very aggressive Pokémon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.

pokemon.name: wurmple
pokemon.text_entry: Wurmple is targeted by Swellow as prey. This Pokémon will try to resist by pointing the spikes on its rear at the attacking predator. It will weaken the foe by leaking poison from the spikes.

pokemon.name: silcoon
pokemon.text_entry: Silcoon was thought to endure hunger and not consume anything before its evolution. However, it is now thought that this Pokémon slakes its thirst by drinking rainwater that collects on its silk.

pokemon.name: beautifly
pokemon.text_entry: Beautifly has a long mouth like a coiled needle, which is very convenient for collecting pollen from flowers. This Pokémon rides the spring winds as it flits around gathering pollen.

pokemon.name: cascoon
pokemon.text_entry: If it is attacked, Cascoon remains motionless however badly it may be hurt. It does so because if it were to move, its body would be weak upon evolution. This Pokémon will also not forget the pain it endured.

pokemon.name: dustox
pokemon.text_entry: When Dustox flaps its wings, a fine dust is scattered all over. This dust is actually a powerful poison that will even make a pro wrestler sick. This Pokémon searches for food using its antennae like radar.

pokemon.name: lotad
pokemon.text_entry: Its leaf grew too large for it to live on land. That is how it began to live floating in the water.

pokemon.name: lombre
pokemon.text_entry: It lives at the water’s edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.

pokemon.name: ludicolo
pokemon.text_entry: If it hears festive music, it begins moving in rhythm in order to amplify its power.

pokemon.name: seedot
pokemon.text_entry: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

pokemon.name: nuzleaf
pokemon.text_entry: They live in holes bored in large trees. The sound of Nuzleaf’s grass flute fills listeners with dread.

pokemon.name: shiftry
pokemon.text_entry: It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.

pokemon.name: taillow
pokemon.text_entry: Taillow is young—it has only just left its nest. As a result, it sometimes becomes lonesome and cries at night. This Pokémon feeds on Wurmple that live in forests.

pokemon.name: swellow
pokemon.text_entry: Swellow is very conscientious about the upkeep of its glossy wings. Once two Swellow are gathered, they diligently take care of cleaning each other’s wings.

pokemon.name: wingull
pokemon.text_entry: It soars on updrafts without flapping its wings. It makes a nest on sheer cliffs at the sea’s edge.

pokemon.name: pelipper
pokemon.text_entry: Skimming the water’s surface, it dips its large bill in the sea, scoops up food and water, and carries it.

pokemon.name: ralts
pokemon.text_entry: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.

pokemon.name: kirlia
pokemon.text_entry: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

pokemon.name: gardevoir
pokemon.text_entry: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

pokemon.name: surskit
pokemon.text_entry: It lives in ponds and marshes that feature lots of plant life. It often fights with Dewpider, whose habitat and diet are similar.

pokemon.name: masquerain
pokemon.text_entry: Its thin, winglike antennae are highly absorbent. It waits out rainy days in tree hollows.

pokemon.name: shroomish
pokemon.text_entry: If Shroomish senses danger, it shakes its body and scatters spores from the top of its head. This Pokémon’s spores are so toxic, they make trees and weeds wilt.

pokemon.name: breloom
pokemon.text_entry: The seeds ringing Breloom’s tail are made of hardened toxic spores. It is horrible to eat the seeds. Just taking a bite of this Pokémon’s seed will cause your stomach to rumble.

pokemon.name: slakoth
pokemon.text_entry: Slakoth’s heart beats just once a minute. Whatever happens, it is content to loaf around motionless. It is rare to see this Pokémon in motion.

pokemon.name: vigoroth
pokemon.text_entry: Vigoroth is simply incapable of remaining still. Even when it tries to sleep, the blood in its veins grows agitated, compelling this Pokémon to run wild throughout the jungle before it can settle down.

pokemon.name: slaking
pokemon.text_entry: Wherever Slaking live, rings of over a yard in diameter appear in grassy fields. They are made by the Pokémon as it eats all the grass within reach while lying prone on the ground.

pokemon.name: nincada
pokemon.text_entry: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

pokemon.name: ninjask
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is so quick, it is said to be able to avoid any attack. It loves to feed on tree sap.

pokemon.name: shedinja
pokemon.text_entry: A strange Pokémon—it flies without moving its wings, has a hollow shell for a body, and does not breathe.

pokemon.name: whismur
pokemon.text_entry: When Whismur cries, the sound of its own voice startles it, making the Pokémon cry even louder. It cries until it’s exhausted, then it falls asleep.

pokemon.name: loudred
pokemon.text_entry: The force of this Pokémon’s loud voice isn’t just the sound—it’s also the wave of air pressure that blows opponents away and damages them.

pokemon.name: exploud
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon can do more than just shout. To communicate with others of its kind, it’ll emit all sorts of sounds from the holes in its body.

pokemon.name: makuhita
pokemon.text_entry: There’s a rumor of a traditional recipe for stew that Trainers can use to raise strong Makuhita.

pokemon.name: hariyama
pokemon.text_entry: Hariyama that are big and fat aren’t necessarily strong. There are some small ones that move nimbly and use moves skillfully.

pokemon.name: azurill
pokemon.text_entry: Although Azurill are normally docile, an angry one will swing around the big ball on its tail and try to smash its opponents.

pokemon.name: nosepass
pokemon.text_entry: It hunts without twitching a muscle by pulling in its prey with powerful magnetism. But sometimes it pulls natural enemies in close.

pokemon.name: skitty
pokemon.text_entry: Skitty is known to chase around playfully after its own tail. In the wild, this Pokémon lives in holes in the trees of forests. It is very popular as a pet because of its adorable looks.

pokemon.name: delcatty
pokemon.text_entry: Delcatty sleeps anywhere it wants without keeping a permanent nest. If other Pokémon approach it as it sleeps, this Pokémon will never fight—it will just move away somewhere else.

pokemon.name: sableye
pokemon.text_entry: It feeds on gemstone crystals. In darkness, its eyes sparkle with the glitter of jewels.

pokemon.name: mawile
pokemon.text_entry: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

pokemon.name: aron
pokemon.text_entry: Aron has a body of steel. With one all-out charge, this Pokémon can demolish even a heavy dump truck. The destroyed dump truck then becomes a handy meal for the Pokémon.

pokemon.name: lairon
pokemon.text_entry: Lairon feeds on iron contained in rocks and water. It makes its nest on mountains where iron ore is buried. As a result, the Pokémon often clashes with humans mining the iron ore.

pokemon.name: aggron
pokemon.text_entry: Aggron is protective of its environment. If its mountain is ravaged by a landslide or a fire, this Pokémon will haul topsoil to the area, plant trees, and beautifully restore its own territory.

pokemon.name: meditite
pokemon.text_entry: Meditite heightens its inner energy through meditation. It survives on just one berry a day. Minimal eating is another aspect of this Pokémon’s training.

pokemon.name: medicham
pokemon.text_entry: Through the power of meditation, Medicham developed its sixth sense. It gained the ability to use psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon is known to meditate for a whole month without eating.

pokemon.name: electrike
pokemon.text_entry: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

pokemon.name: manectric
pokemon.text_entry: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.

pokemon.name: plusle
pokemon.text_entry: When Plusle is cheering on its partner, it flashes with electric sparks from all over its body. If its partner loses, this Pokémon cries loudly.

pokemon.name: minun
pokemon.text_entry: Minun loves to cheer on its partner in battle. It gives off sparks from its body while it is doing so. If its partner is in trouble, this Pokémon gives off increasing amounts of sparks.

pokemon.name: volbeat
pokemon.text_entry: Volbeat’s tail glows like a lightbulb. With other Volbeat, it uses its tail to draw geometric shapes in the night sky. This Pokémon loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.

pokemon.name: illumise
pokemon.text_entry: Illumise leads a flight of illuminated Volbeat to draw signs in the night sky. This Pokémon is said to earn greater respect from its peers by composing more complex designs in the sky.

pokemon.name: roselia
pokemon.text_entry: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

pokemon.name: gulpin
pokemon.text_entry: Most of Gulpin’s body is made up of its stomach—its heart and brain are very small in comparison. This Pokémon’s stomach contains special enzymes that dissolve anything.

pokemon.name: swalot
pokemon.text_entry: Swalot has no teeth, so what it eats, it swallows whole, no matter what. Its cavernous mouth yawns widely. An automobile tire could easily fit inside this Pokémon’s mouth.

pokemon.name: carvanha
pokemon.text_entry: These Pokémon have sharp fangs and powerful jaws. Sailors avoid Carvanha dens at all costs.

pokemon.name: sharpedo
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sea. Any ship entering the waters Sharpedo calls home will be attacked—no exceptions.

pokemon.name: wailmer
pokemon.text_entry: When it sucks in a large volume of seawater, it becomes like a big, bouncy ball. It eats a ton of food daily.

pokemon.name: wailord
pokemon.text_entry: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

pokemon.name: numel
pokemon.text_entry: Numel stores magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit within its body. If it gets wet, the magma cools and hardens. In that event, the Pokémon’s body grows heavy and its movements become sluggish.

pokemon.name: camerupt
pokemon.text_entry: The humps on Camerupt’s back are formed by a transformation of its bones. They sometimes blast out molten magma. This Pokémon apparently erupts often when it is enraged.

pokemon.name: torkoal
pokemon.text_entry: You find abandoned coal mines full of them. They dig tirelessly in search of coal.

pokemon.name: spoink
pokemon.text_entry: Spoink keeps a pearl on top of its head. The pearl functions to amplify this Pokémon’s psychokinetic powers. It is therefore on a constant search for a bigger pearl.

pokemon.name: grumpig
pokemon.text_entry: Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to wield its fantastic powers. When it is doing so, it dances bizarrely. This Pokémon’s black pearls are valuable as works of art.

pokemon.name: spinda
pokemon.text_entry: Each Spinda’s spot pattern is different. With its stumbling movements, it evades opponents’ attacks brilliantly!

pokemon.name: trapinch
pokemon.text_entry: It makes an inescapable conical pit and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

pokemon.name: vibrava
pokemon.text_entry: To help make its wings grow, it dissolves quantities of prey in its digestive juices and guzzles them down every day.

pokemon.name: flygon
pokemon.text_entry: It is nicknamed the Desert Spirit because the flapping of its wings sounds like a woman singing.

pokemon.name: cacnea
pokemon.text_entry: The more arid and harsh the environment, the more pretty and fragrant a flower Cacnea grows. This Pokémon battles by wildly swinging its thorny arms.

pokemon.name: cacturne
pokemon.text_entry: If a traveler is going through a desert in the thick of night, Cacturne will follow in a ragtag group. The Pokémon are biding their time, waiting for the traveler to tire and become incapable of moving.

pokemon.name: swablu
pokemon.text_entry: Swablu loves to make things clean. If it spots something dirty, it will wipe and polish it with its cottony wings. If its wings become dirty, this Pokémon finds a stream and showers itself.

pokemon.name: altaria
pokemon.text_entry: Altaria sings in a gorgeous soprano. Its wings are like cotton clouds. This Pokémon catches updrafts with its buoyant wings and soars way up into the wild blue yonder.

pokemon.name: zangoose
pokemon.text_entry: Zangoose usually stays on all fours, but when angered, it gets up on its hind legs and extends its claws. This Pokémon shares a bitter rivalry with Seviper that dates back over generations.

pokemon.name: seviper
pokemon.text_entry: Seviper’s swordlike tail serves two purposes—it slashes foes and douses them with secreted poison. This Pokémon will not give up its long-running blood feud with Zangoose.

pokemon.name: lunatone
pokemon.text_entry: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.

pokemon.name: solrock
pokemon.text_entry: Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.

pokemon.name: barboach
pokemon.text_entry: It probes muddy riverbeds with its two long whiskers. A slimy film protects its body.

pokemon.name: whiscash
pokemon.text_entry: It claims a large swamp to itself. If a foe comes near it, it sets off tremors by thrashing around.

pokemon.name: corphish
pokemon.text_entry: It was originally a Pokémon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.

pokemon.name: crawdaunt
pokemon.text_entry: A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

pokemon.name: baltoy
pokemon.text_entry: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

pokemon.name: claydol
pokemon.text_entry: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

pokemon.name: lileep
pokemon.text_entry: It sticks to rocks with its powerful suckers and can’t be washed away no matter how rough the surf gets.

pokemon.name: cradily
pokemon.text_entry: This carnivorous Pokémon lived in primordial seas. It catches prey in its eight tentacles and dissolves them with digestive fluid as it eats.

pokemon.name: anorith
pokemon.text_entry: This is one kind of primeval bug Pokémon. With eight wings, it could apparently swim a lot faster than you’d expect.

pokemon.name: armaldo
pokemon.text_entry: Armaldo adapted from living in water to living on land. It has been determined that it is the ancestor of some bug Pokémon.

pokemon.name: feebas
pokemon.text_entry: It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.

pokemon.name: milotic
pokemon.text_entry: It’s said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you’re feeling.

pokemon.name: castform
pokemon.text_entry: Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform’s disposition!

pokemon.name: kecleon
pokemon.text_entry: Its color changes for concealment and also when its mood or health changes. The darker the color, the healthier it is.

pokemon.name: shuppet
pokemon.text_entry: There’s a proverb that says, “Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk.”

pokemon.name: banette
pokemon.text_entry: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.

pokemon.name: duskull
pokemon.text_entry: Making itself invisible, it silently sneaks up to prey. It has the ability to slip through thick walls.

pokemon.name: dusclops
pokemon.text_entry: It seeks drifting will-o’-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.

pokemon.name: tropius
pokemon.text_entry: Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.

pokemon.name: chimecho
pokemon.text_entry: In high winds, Chimecho cries as it hangs from a tree branch or the eaves of a building using a suction cup on its head. This Pokémon plucks berries with its long tail and eats them.

pokemon.name: absol
pokemon.text_entry: The elderly call it the disaster Pokémon and detest it, but interest in its power to predict disasters is on the rise.

pokemon.name: wynaut
pokemon.text_entry: It tends to move in a pack with others. They cluster in a tight group to sleep in a cave.

pokemon.name: snorunt
pokemon.text_entry: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as −150 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: glalie
pokemon.text_entry: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.

pokemon.name: spheal
pokemon.text_entry: Spheal always travels by rolling around on its ball-like body. When the season for ice floes arrives, this Pokémon can be seen rolling about on ice and crossing the sea.

pokemon.name: sealeo
pokemon.text_entry: Sealeo often balances and rolls things on the tip of its nose. While the Pokémon is rolling something, it checks the object’s aroma and texture to determine whether it likes the object or not.

pokemon.name: walrein
pokemon.text_entry: Walrein swims all over in frigid seawater while crushing icebergs with its grand, imposing tusks. Its thick layer of blubber makes enemy attacks bounce off harmlessly.

pokemon.name: clamperl
pokemon.text_entry: Clamperl’s pearls are exceedingly precious. They can be more than 10 times as costly as Shellder’s pearls.

pokemon.name: huntail
pokemon.text_entry: Deep seas are their habitat. According to tradition, when Huntail wash up onshore, something unfortunate will happen.

pokemon.name: gorebyss
pokemon.text_entry: It sucks bodily fluids out of its prey. The leftover meat sinks to the seafloor, where it becomes food for other Pokémon.

pokemon.name: relicanth
pokemon.text_entry: The reason it hasn’t changed at all in a hundred million years is that it’s apparently already a perfect life-form.

pokemon.name: luvdisc
pokemon.text_entry: Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola’s branches.

pokemon.name: bagon
pokemon.text_entry: Some theories suggest that its behavior of forcefully bashing its head into things stimulates cells that affect its evolution.

pokemon.name: shelgon
pokemon.text_entry: Shelgon lives deep within caves. It stays shut up in its hard shell, dreaming of the day it will be able to fly.

pokemon.name: salamence
pokemon.text_entry: Thanks to its fervent wishes, the cells in its body finally mutated, and at last it has its heart’s desire—wings.

pokemon.name: beldum
pokemon.text_entry: If you anger it, it will do more than rampage. It will also burst out strong magnetism, causing nearby machines to break.

pokemon.name: metang
pokemon.text_entry: It flies at high speeds around the skies. When it finds its prey, Metang takes a firm grip with its sharp claws and never lets go.

pokemon.name: metagross
pokemon.text_entry: It analyzes its opponents with more accuracy than a supercomputer, which enables it to calmly back them into a corner.

pokemon.name: regirock
pokemon.text_entry: Regirock’s body is composed entirely of rocks. Recently, a study made the startling discovery that the rocks were all unearthed from different locations.

pokemon.name: regice
pokemon.text_entry: Regice cloaks itself with frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit. Things will freeze solid just by going near this Pokémon. Its icy body is so cold, it will not melt even if it is immersed in magma.

pokemon.name: registeel
pokemon.text_entry: Registeel was imprisoned by people in ancient times. The metal composing its body is thought to be a curious substance that is not of this earth.

pokemon.name: latias
pokemon.text_entry: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

pokemon.name: latios
pokemon.text_entry: Latios will only open its heart to a Trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

pokemon.name: kyogre
pokemon.text_entry: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

pokemon.name: groudon
pokemon.text_entry: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.

pokemon.name: rayquaza
pokemon.text_entry: It flies forever through the ozone layer, consuming meteoroids for sustenance. The many meteoroids in its body provide the energy it needs to Mega Evolve.

pokemon.name: jirachi
pokemon.text_entry: It’s believed that when this Pokémon wakes from its 1,000-year slumber, it will grant any wishes written on the notes attached to its head.

pokemon.name: deoxys-normal
pokemon.text_entry: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.
